President Donald Trump has declared a national emergency to address the border security and humanitarian crisis at the United States' southern border. This declaration allows the Secretary of Defense and relevant military departments to order units or members of the Ready Reserve to active duty in order to support the activities of the Secretary of Homeland Security. Additionally, the President has authorized the Secretary of Defense, and at his discretion, the Secretaries of the military departments, to engage in emergency construction to support the use of the Armed Forces and respond to the crisis. President Trump has enclosed a copy of the Proclamation he has issued.